summary: The First Pokemon Company Officiated Wedding Was a Success
title: The First Pokemon Company Officiated Wedding Was a Success
body:
A few months ago, The Pokemon Company linked up with ESCRIT to offer full-out Pokemon themed weddings and the first official wedding of the collaboration just happened.

The picture above was posted by the couple on Twitter and here’s what they had to say about the event.

“The wedding is over! It was a great honor for the world’s first wedding organized by the official Pokémon, and it was so much fun! Thank you all for coming! It was a great day I could never forget!“

Now we want to know, would you have a Pokemon themed wedding? 

BUY: Detective Pikachu Plush ($24)

summary: Have you seen Detective Pikachu or are you planning on seeing it?
question: Have you seen Detective Pikachu or are you planning on seeing it?
answer:
I HAVE! YES I HAVE! Twice.

Well..I really liked it a lot, the aesthetics, the way they translated Pokemon to the real world was pretty good, so good on them for that, although some Pokemon looked horrendous, Machamp was the best example for that, the CG on him looked SOOOO terrible, Bulbasaur and Squirtlle’s one wasn’t very good unfortunately…the others thought, almost perfect.

It had a lot of bad things though, the story has tons of plot convinience moments, TONS of them, it doesn’t explain some things, it kinda implies the main character was a pokemon trainer but it doesn’t really clarify it well enough, also when was it stablished that Mewtwo could soultransfer things into people?

The main bad guy is SO predictable, from the moment you know who he is which is not very good, overall the script was not very worked out, however…I can’t really be harsh on it, they just wanted to make something entertaining, and on that regard it works, just as the Pokemon movies made from the anime so….I don’t hate them for it, I enjoyed my time in there.

It’s not the best videogame movies as some peolpe are saying, but it’s miles above the standar videogame movie.

summary: I just saw Detective Pikachu
title: I just saw Detective Pikachu
body:
And watched carefully the credits, and I already forgot the name of the guy who did a 7-beats-a-measure theme for this movie. He’s a genius.

Also I expected something stunning, I had it. It wasn’t even too loud, which is rare for a movie in cinema.
I usually don’t like movies, especially when on a cinema screen. But this one. This would have been wasting to watch it on your TV or phone. If you have a chance to watch it now, go.
